tic hormone","Growth hormone","Follicle stimulating hormone","Adrenocorticotropic hormone","Luteinizing hormone"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESomatostatin is an inhibitory hormone that suppresses the release of several hormones in the body - including \u003Cstrong\u003Egrowth hormone\u003C/strong\u003E release, which is strongly inhibited by somatostatin. \u003Cstrong\u003EAntidiuretic hormone, follicle stimulating hormone\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eadrenocorticotropic hormone\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Eluteinizing hormone\u003C/strong\u003E are not directly inhibited by somatostatin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESomatostatin\u0027s main effects include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInhibition of growth hormone, prolactin and thyroid stimulating hormone from the anterior pituitary\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInhibition of insulin and glucagon from pancreatic islets\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInhibition of gastrin, secretin, and cholecystokinin from the gastrointestinal tract\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGeneral reduction in gastrointestinal motility and secretion\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Somatostatin inhibits the release of growth hormone, prolactin and thyroid stimulating hormone from the anterior pituitary gland","Somatostatin inhibits the release of insulin and glucagon from the pancreatic islets","Somatostatin inhibits the release of gastrin, secretin, and cholecystokinin from the gastrointestinal tract"],"references":["Bloom SR, Polak JM. Somatostatin. Br Med J (Clin Res Ed). 1987 Aug 1;295(6593):288-90. doi: 10.1136/bmj.295.6593.288. PMID: 2888511; PMCID: PMC1247137.","O\u0027Toole TJ, Sharma S. Physiology, Somatostatin. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538327/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52688"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15617"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52688"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T09:40:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T09:42:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8308"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67236"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},